Women’s organisations put a lot of energy into organising events where human rights and women’s groups come together to draft model policy documents on women’s rights. Public participation activities with actual practical outcomes that aim at raising awareness of men in particular about rights violations towards women are scarce.

The Cyprus Organisation of Women’s Associations was established in 1989 with a one-hundredwomen-led membership. The organisation is active in providing a forum for the freexchange of views and experiences on matters of legislation that affect women; encouraging and stimulating research and learning; providing social, cultural and scientific activities; addressing women’s needs, reflecting women’s problems and protecting women’s rights and interests.
The Cyprus Family Planning Association (CFPA) values the centrality of women’s empowerment to everyone’s well - being. This means involving women in political and social life, promoting their access to power and resources and defending the principles of gender equality, in order to overcome gender-based discrimination .
